 title: 'Regulatory Capture Under Trump',
 subtitle: 'Industry insiders destroying EPA, OSHA, CFPB, and protective agencies',
 severity: 'high',
 category: 'Corruption',
 date: 'June 19, 2017',
 lastUpdated: 'September 26, 2024',
 summary: 'The Trump administration systematically installed industry executives and lobbyists to run the agencies that regulate their industries. The result was regulatory capture, agencies protecting industry interests rather than the public. Environmental protections were gutted, worker safety ignored, consumer protections rolled back, and corporate interests prioritized over public health and safety.',
 content: [
 'EPA UNDER PRUITT AND WHEELER: Scott Pruitt and Andrew Wheeler, both with deep fossil fuel ties, ran the EPA. They rolled back over 100 environmental rules including clean air standards, water protections, and climate regulations. Pruitt resigned amid ethics scandals.',
 'CLEAN POWER PLAN REPEAL: The EPA repealed Obama\'s Clean Power Plan limiting power plant emissions. The replacement "Affordable Clean Energy "rule was so weak it was struck down by courts. Climate action was reversed.',
 'MERCURY RULE GUTTED: The EPA reversed the finding that limiting mercury and other toxic emissions from power plants was"appropriate and necessary."The rule had prevented thousands of premature deaths annually.',
 'OSHA NEGLIGENCE: OSHA under Trump issued no significant safety rules, dramatically reduced inspections, and imposed minimal penalties even for worker deaths. During COVID, OSHA refused to issue emergency standards protecting workers.',
 'MEATPACKING DEATHS: When COVID swept through meatpacking plants killing workers, the administration issued an executive order keeping plants open. OSHA failed to protect workers. Companies received liability immunity.',
 'CFPB GUTTING: Mick Mulvaney, who had called the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau a "joke," was appointed to run it. He froze enforcement, dropped investigations, and tried to zero out the agency\'s budget.',
 'PAYDAY LENDING: The CFPB rolled back rules protecting consumers from predatory payday lenders. Industry groups who had fought the rules praised the changes. Vulnerable borrowers lost protections.',
 'INTERIOR DEPARTMENT: Interior was run by officials with ties to oil, gas, and coal industries. They opened public lands to drilling, weakened endangered species protections, and reduced Bears Ears National Monument by 85%.',
 'HHS AND PHARMA: HHS officials with pharmaceutical industry ties oversaw drug pricing policy. Despite promises to lower drug prices, the administration\'s policies often benefited industry.',
 'USDA UNDER PERDUE: Sonny Perdue moved USDA research agencies out of Washington, causing mass staff exodus. Research on climate change impacts on agriculture was suppressed. Industry-friendly policies advanced.',
 'DOL UNDER ACOSTA: Alex Acosta (who had given Jeffrey Epstein a sweetheart plea deal) ran the Labor Department. Worker protections declined. Overtime rules were weakened. Enforcement dropped.',
 'THE PATTERN: Across agencies, Trump appointed industry insiders who implemented industry wish lists. Regulations protecting health, safety, environment, and consumers were systematically dismantled.',
 ],
